parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or wobbles violently
the steering wheel becomes difficult to control
the vehicle pulls to one side
the front end of the vehicle shakes or vibrates
and the vehicle becomes unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tie rod can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The tie rod separates from the tire
the vehicle shakes or wobbles violently
the steering wheel becomes difficult to control
and the vehicle becomes unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to repair or diagnose steering issues can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle has been recalled for steering issues
but the parts are unavailable
or the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag inflator can cause the airbag to deploy improperly or not deploy at all, leading to serious injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Airbags did not deploy in a crash
airbag warning light illuminated
inability to get recall repair due to parts unavailability
delayed or lack of notification about recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of recall repairs can leave vehicles on the road with potentially deadly defects, putting drivers and passengers at risk of serious injury or death.
symptoms: Parts not available for recall repair
long wait times for repair
lack of notification about recall repair
inability to schedule repair appointment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle can roll away, causing accidents or property damage, and potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls away while in park
the transmission shifts into reverse or neutral without warning
the vehicle accelerates in reverse
and the parking pawl does not engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch pedal can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle and transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The drive shaft dislodges from the vehicle
the rear axle and transmission fail
and the vehicle vibrates abnormally.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system and electrical components can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The horn sounds and warning indicators flicker independently
and the airbag inflator recall was not performed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power train and transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission shifts into reverse or neutral without warning
the vehicle accelerates in reverse
and the parking pawl does not engage.
